Cumulus Creates Core Activations in Data Cloud

To build their data foundation, the Cumulus team creates Data Cloud activations for their audiences to Marketing Cloud Engagement. These activations comprise their data foundation.

Review Create a segment in Data Cloud

In Data Cloud, on the Segments tab, click New.
Name the segment Full Core Individual Audience and add a description.
Select a publishing schedule of 12 hours.
Click Edit Rules.
From the attributes list, find the DMO for Individual and Data Source attributes and drag Data Source to the interface.
Set the operator to Is Equal To.
To qualify contacts in your Marketing Cloud Engagement account, enter your company’s enterprise ID. For example, SFMC1079707.
NOTE Your company’s enterprise ID is unique. You can also add other criteria to qualify your full audience.
Click Done and then click Save.
If applicable, repeat these steps to create Unified Individual segments.
